## Accommodation Types
**What types of accommodations does the space hotel network offer?**
- Orbital Suites: private cabins aboard low-Earth orbit stations (400-500 km altitude), featuring panoramic Earth-view windows and zero-gravity sleeping pods
- Lunar Surface Bungalows: pressurized habitat units on the lunar surface near the Mare Tranquillitatis base; standard gravity simulation available
- Transit Pods: compact single or double-occupancy cabins for guests in transit between Earth and lunar destinations; minimum stay 1 night
- Presidential Orbital Villas: full-deck private suites with dedicated crew, available on select stations only

## Pre-Flight Requirements
**What does a guest need before they can book a stay?**
- Valid health clearance certificate issued by a certified aerospace medical examiner (must not expire before the travel return date)
- Zero-G training certification (8-hour course) required for all orbital and transit bookings; not required for lunar surface bungalows with gravity simulation
- Minimum age: 18 years; guests aged 18-21 require a co-traveling adult guardian
- Travel insurance covering orbital evacuation is strongly recommended but not mandatory

## Pricing & Payment
**How is pricing structured for space hotel stays?**
- Nightly rates are quoted in USD and exclude launch transport costs
- Launch transport is booked separately through affiliated launch providers
- Packages (spacewalk, excursions, meal plans) are priced as flat add-ons per guest
- Stellar Tier members (Silver, Gold, Nebula) receive 5%, 10%, and 15% discounts respectively on base room rates
- Full payment is required at time of booking; payment plans available for reservations over 100,000 USD

## Cancellation & Refund Policy
**What is the cancellation policy?**
- More than 90 days before check-in: 100% refund
- 30 to 90 days before check-in: 50% refund
- Less than 30 days before check-in: no refund
- Cancellations due to a failed health clearance renewal are eligible for a one-time date change at no penalty
- Launch window cancellations initiated by the hotel result in a full refund plus a 10% credit toward a future booking

## Stellar Tier Loyalty Program
**How does the Stellar Tier loyalty program work?**
- Enrollment is automatic after a guest's first completed stay
- Tiers: Silver (1-2 stays), Gold (3-5 stays), Nebula (6+ stays)
- Benefits include room rate discounts, priority launch window access, complimentary package upgrades, and dedicated concierge lines
- Tier status is reviewed annually; stays must be completed within a rolling 24-month window to maintain tier level

## Spacewalk & Excursion Packages
**What add-on experiences are available?**
- Guided EVA Spacewalk (orbital stations only): 3-hour extravehicular activity with certified guide; requires additional EVA safety briefing on arrival
- Lunar Rover Excursion (lunar surface only): 4-hour surface drive to crater rim viewpoints; maximum 4 guests per rover
- Astronomical Observation Session: 2-hour private telescope session with onboard astrophysicist; available at all locations
- Zero-G Culinary Experience: chef-prepared multi-course meal in microgravity; orbital stations only
- All packages must be booked at least 14 days before departure

## Launch Windows
**How do launch windows work and how often do they occur?**
- Launch windows are fixed departure and return slots from designated Earth launch sites (currently: Kennedy Space Center, Baikonur, Tanegashima)
- Windows to orbital stations occur approximately every 48-72 hours depending on orbital mechanics
- Windows to lunar destinations occur every 7-10 days aligned with transit trajectory optimization
- Each window has a fixed passenger capacity; availability is confirmed in real time during booking
- Guests must arrive at the launch site 12 hours before the scheduled departure window

## Health Clearance Renewal
**What should a guest do if their health clearance is expiring before their trip?**
- Contact a certified aerospace medical examiner at least 60 days before travel to allow processing time
- The hotel can provide a list of approved examiners by region upon request
- If clearance cannot be renewed due to a new medical condition, the guest may be eligible for a penalty-free date change (see cancellation policy)
- Guests with expired clearance at time of booking will be flagged and cannot proceed until a valid clearance date is confirmed